The paper deals with the problem of recovering sparse signals from incomplete measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of mixed l^1/l^2-minimization is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.NA). The paper also involves the study of coherence parameters and restricted isometry property, which are relevant in the field of compressed sensing (cs.SI).
